0:{}s:9:"sentences";a:69:{i:0;s:133:"Use this model letter to inform an employee who has resigned that they are to be placed on garden leave throughout the notice period.";i:1;s:206:"A garden leave clause forms part of an employee’s contract of employment, the employer may elect to relieve the employee from performing his/ her duties for the duration of any notice period, on full pay.";i:2;s:162:"Garden leave “garden leave” is the term given to a situation whereby an employee is required to serve out a period of notice at home (or “in the garden”).";i:3;s:126:"Garden leave refers to the process where you spend part (or the full) duration of your notice period away from the office, on.";i:4;s:64:"Instead, the employee is paid their full salary to stay at home.";i:5;s:75:"To help us improve gov.uk, we’d like to know more about your visit today.";i:6;s:72:"While we can connect you with some very fine advisers in the uk, and we.";i:7;s:139:"In placing the employee on garden leave, the employer must not do anything that could amount to a breach of the contract with the employee.";i:8;s:134:"Communicate the decision to relevant staff, including details of whether the employee will be contactable if they are on garden leave.";i:9;s:39:"Garden leave and restrictive covenants.";i:10;s:148:"Xperthr defines garden leave as the practice of requiring an employee not to attend their employer’s premises for work during their notice period.";i:11;s:40:"Letter to confirm employee garden leave.";i:12;s:44:"We explain your rights and responsibilities.";i:13;s:70:"Check to see if there are contractual clauses that allow you to do so;";i:14;s:175:"This letter placing an employee on garden leave following resignation should be used by an employer who has the express contractual right to place an employee on garden leave.";i:15;s:170:"Garden leave means that, although the employee does not attend work during the notice period, he or she remains an employee on full contractual benefits for the duration.";i:16;s:82:"Letter responding to an employee's resignation requiring a period of garden leave.";i:17;s:126:"A model letter to inform an employee who has resigned that they are to be placed on garden leave throughout the notice period.";i:18;s:43:"We’ll send you a link to a feedback form.";i:19;s:186:"During this period the employee continues to receive all salary and benefits but is prohibited from commencing employment with new employers until the gardening leave period has expired.";i:20;s:33:"Why is it called gardening leave?";i:21;s:37:"Dear [name of employee] garden leave.";i:22;s:146:"A garden leave clause may be in addition to restrictive covenants, which restrict the employee’s activities once employment has been terminated.";i:23;s:115:"Even if you do, it’s still good business practice to provide your employee with a letter explaining your process.";i:24;s:28:"Garden leave and holiday pay";i:25;s:176:"Moreover, during garden leave, the employer is under no obligation to provide work or assign any duties to the employee for the whole or part of the employee’s notice period.";i:26;s:151:"In this short guide, we consider what exactly it is, what practical implications it may have for you, and what your rights are if you are placed on it.";i:27;s:132:"This letter explains the employee's obligations to the organisation while they are on garden leave and when the garden leave starts.";i:28;s:130:"Garden leave can also be instigated at the employee's request (if it suits you too) or as part of negotiated terms over departure.";i:29;s:64:"Letter placing an employee on garden leave following resignation";i:30;s:191:"You must make sure either that the employee’s contract of employment gives you a specific and enforceable right to use garden leave or the employee agrees in advance, preferably in writing.";i:31;s:145:"The employee must stay away from work during the whole or part of his notice period but continues to be employed and to receive pay and benefits.";i:32;s:47:"Mr christensen was the vice president of sales.";i:33;s:65:"Letter placing an employee on garden leave following resignation.";i:34;s:157:"This document contains the paragraphs dealing with garden leave, restrictive covenants and associated matters which can be included in a letter dismissing a.";i:35;s:114:"Policies and documents letter informing a competitor of the contractual obligations of an employee on garden leave";i:36;s:111:"Set out the details of the arrangement (including any conditions of garden leave) in a letter to your employee;";i:37;s:100:"Garden leave letter template you may already have a clause in your contract explaining garden leave.";i:38;s:142:"I acknowledge receipt of your letter dated [date] resigning your position as [job title] with the company with effect from [termination date].";i:39;s:22:"Looking for a new job.";i:40;s:64:"But is it a good thing or could it damage your career prospects?";i:41;s:146:"While on garden leave, employees still have the rights of a normal employee of the company and there are a number of activities available to them.";i:42;s:65:"Some of the actions an employee on garden leave can take include:";i:43;s:61:"If you need advice on garden leave or pilon, do get in touch.";i:44;s:199:"Garden leave is basically a device which an employer can use to help protect itself against possible mischief by an employee during his notice period when the employee has resigned or been dismissed.";i:45;s:95:"The employee may also be required to take their accrued holiday during the garden leave period.";i:46;s:82:"Letter responding to an employee's resignation requiring a period of garden leave.";i:47;s:151:"It’s also used to keep the former employee away from clients and customers or to prevent the resigning employee from encouraging others to join them.";i:48;s:53:"Jo stubbs when to use this model garden leave letter.";i:49;s:178:"You should use this letter when an employee has resigned and you want to put them on garden leave, rather than require them to attend the office and work out their notice period.";i:50;s:39:"It will take only 2 minutes to fill in.";i:51;s:131:"For all intents and purposes, during the garden leave, the employee remains an employee and must remain accessible to the employer.";i:52;s:152:"Gardening leave is often used by employers wanting to protect themselves against competition or poaching of customers, clients, or staff by an employee.";i:53;s:107:"But the same rules apply—the employee may not begin new employment until the garden leave period is over.";i:54;s:134:"The symbian v christensen case of 2000 is probably one of the most notable employment law cases concerning garden leave to ever occur.";i:55;s:114:"On garden leave, in all cases in which the contract of employment imposes on the employer an obligation to permit.";i:56;s:66:"You can put an employee you’re making redundant on garden leave.";i:57;s:181:"Garden leave is used to keep the resigning employee away from confidential data and sensitive information (it also limits what they can pass on if they’re moving to a competitor).";i:58;s:96:"It can only be enforced on you once you have resigned with notice or been dismissed with notice.";i:59;s:46:"6 pages) ask a question letter on termination:";i:60;s:32:"View all § garden leave letter.";i:61;s:158:"The meaning of garden leave (often known as ‘gardening leave’), is that you require the employee to be away from the workplace during their notice period.";i:62;s:86:"Letter placing employee on garden leave following resignation (no data leak concerns).";i:63;s:53:"Before placing an employee on garden leave, you must:";i:64;s:90:"You can do this from the time their notice period starts up until they leave the business.";i:65;s:216:"It is known as gardening leave, or garden leave, because while employees may not be required to work for their employers and are almost always not allowed to work for another employer or themselves, they are allowed.";i:66;s:38:"Why are people placed on garden leave?";i:67;s:230:"In the leading case concerning an employer’s right to place an employee on garden leave the court of appeal said “in practice, an employer will need to stipulate for an express power to send his employee home on full pay, i.e.";i:68;s:164:"If you’ve recently handed in your letter of resignation, been suspended from your role, or been made an offer for redundancy, you could be placed on garden leave.";}}